**selectrows.min.js** is a JavaScript library that manages row selection within tables using checkboxes. 

It provides "select all" functionality, handles grouped selections, and updates input fields with the IDs of selected rows. 

This enhances user interaction and streamlines data handling on web pages.


#### 1. Setting Up Your Input

You need an input box where the IDs of the selected rows will be placed.
Typically, such an input is `hidden`.

`<input type="hidden" class="input input-small" name="ids" id="ids" value='' />`

Every time you check or uncheck a row, such an input box will be updated.

#### 2. Set a Select-All CheckBox

Into a `th` element, create a checkbox with class `select-al-rows`:

```html
<table class="table table-bordered table-condensed fix" width="3000px;">
  <thead class="table-light position-sticky" style="top: -1px; z-index: 1020;">
    <tr>
      <th style="width:50px;">
        <input type="checkbox" class="checkbox select-all-rows" data-input-id="ids" data-rows-group-id="users">
      </th>
```

- The value of `data-input-id` is the id of the input box where to store the IDs of the selected rows.

- The value of `data-rows-group-id` is important if you want to manage more than one table, with more than one group of checkboxes.

#### 3. Set a CheckBox on Each Row

On each row of your table, you have to define a checkbox class `select-row` and a unique ID. 

```html
<input type="checkbox" class="checkbox select-row" id="..." data-id="..." data-rows-group-id="users">
```



